{{Confused|寺内町}}

'''Teramachi''' (寺町) refers to areas in Japan where [[temples]] are concentrated. This name can be found in cities across Japan. In many [[castle towns]], temples and [[cemeteries]] were grouped on the outskirts of the city to form a defensive line in case of enemy attacks.

== Major Teramachi Locations ==
; Tohoku Region
* [[Aomori Prefecture]]: [[Hirosaki]] - Nishishigemori area ({{ill|Zenrin Street|ja|禅林街}}), {{ill|Niideramachi|ja|新寺町 (弘前市)}} area
* [[Miyagi Prefecture]]: [[Sendai]] - {{ill|Shintera|ja|新寺 (若林区)}}, Wakabayashi Ward
* [[Akita Prefecture]]: [[Akita City]] - {{ill|Kyokuhoku|ja|旭北寺町}} area

; Kanto Region
* [[Chiba Prefecture]]: [[Funabashi]] - {{ill|Motomachi Teramachi|ja|本町寺町}}
* [[Tokyo]]:
  * [[Minato City]] - {{ill|Mita|ja|三田 (東京都港区)}} Fourth Chome (see [[Tsukino Misaki]])
  * [[Taito City]] - {{ill|Yanaka|ja|谷中 (台東区)}}
  * [[Setagaya]] - {{ill|Karasuyama Teramachi|ja|烏山寺町}}
  * [[Hachioji]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Hachioji)|ja|寺町 (八王子市)}}

; Chubu Region
* [[Niigata Prefecture]]:
  * [[Joetsu]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Joetsu)|ja|寺町 (上越市)}}
  * [[Itoigawa]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Itoigawa)|ja|寺町 (糸魚川市)}}
  * [[Sado]] (Aikawa) - {{ill|Kamiteramachi|ja|相川町|lt=上寺町}}, {{ill|Nakashiteramachi|ja|中寺町}}, {{ill|Shimoteramachi|ja|下寺町}}. Kamiteramachi is in ruins but part of the [[National Historic Site]] {{ill|Sado Kinzan|ja|佐渡金山}}. Nakashiteramachi and Shimoteramachi are part of the [[Important Cultural Landscape]] {{ill|Cultural Landscape of Aikawa|ja|佐渡相川の鉱山及び鉱山町の文化的景観}} and included in the World Heritage Site {{ill|Sado Island Gold Mines|ja|佐渡島の金山}}.
* [[Ishikawa Prefecture]]: [[Kanazawa]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Kanazawa)|ja|寺町 (金沢市)}}
* [[Gifu Prefecture]]: [[Gifu]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Gifu)|ja|寺町 (岐阜市)}}
* [[Aichi Prefecture]]: [[Handa]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Handa)|ja|寺町 (半田市)}}
* [[Mie Prefecture]]: [[Kuwana]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Kuwana)|ja|寺町 (桑名市)}}

; Kinki Region
* [[Kyoto Prefecture]]:
  * [[Kyoto City]]:
    * {{ill|Teramachi Street|ja|寺町通}} (Nakagyo Ward, Kamigyo Ward)
    * {{ill|Ura Teramachi Street|ja|裏寺町通}} (Nakagyo Ward)
    * {{ill|Teranochi|ja|寺之内}} (Kamigyo Ward)
* [[Osaka Prefecture]]:
  * [[Osaka City]]:
    * Kita Ward - {{ill|Doshin|ja|同心}}, {{ill|Yorikicho|ja|与力町}}, {{ill|Suehirocho|ja|末広町}}, {{ill|Nozakinomachi|ja|兎我野町}}
    * Chuo Ward - {{ill|Uemachi West|ja|上本町西}}, {{ill|Tanimachi|ja|谷町}}, {{ill|Nakatera|ja|中寺}}
    * Tennoji Ward - {{ill|Esashicho|ja|餌差町}}, {{ill|Jonan Teramachi|ja|城南寺町}}, {{ill|Higashikozucho|ja|東高津町}}, {{ill|Uemachi|ja|上本町}}, {{ill|Ikutama|ja|生玉町}}, {{ill|Shimoteramachi|ja|下寺町 (大阪市)}}, {{ill|Yuhigaoka|ja|夕陽丘町}}, {{ill|Rokumandaimachi|ja|六万体町}}
  * [[Sakai]] - {{ill|Teramachisuji|ja|寺町筋}} (Sakai Ward)
* [[Hyogo Prefecture]]: [[Amagasaki]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Amagasaki)|ja|寺町 (尼崎市)}}
* [[Wakayama Prefecture]]: [[Wakayama City]] - {{ill|Fukiage Teramachi|ja|吹上寺町}}

; Chugoku Region
* [[Tottori Prefecture]]: [[Tottori]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Tottori)|ja|寺町 (鳥取市)}}
* [[Shimane Prefecture]]: [[Matsue]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Matsue)|ja|寺町 (松江市)}}
* [[Hiroshima Prefecture]]: [[Hiroshima]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Hiroshima)|ja|寺町 (広島市)}}

; Shikoku Region
* [[Tokushima Prefecture]]:
  * [[Tokushima City]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Tokushima)|ja|寺町 (徳島市)}}
  * [[Mima]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Mima)|ja|寺町 (美馬市)}}

; Kyushu Region
* [[Fukuoka Prefecture]]:
  * [[Fukuoka City]] - {{ill|Gokushocho|ja|御供所町}}, {{ill|Kamigofukucho|ja|上呉服町}}
