{{Confused|Jinaimachi}}

'''Teramachi''' (寺町) refers to areas in Japan where [[temples]] are concentrated. This name can be found in cities across Japan. In many [[castle towns]], temples and [[cemeteries]] were grouped on the outskirts of the city to form a defensive line in case of enemy attacks.

== Major Teramachi Locations ==
; Tohoku Region
* [[Aomori Prefecture]]: [[Hirosaki]] - Nishishigemori area ({{ill|Zenrin Street|ja|禅林街|12=draft}}), {{ill|Niideramachi|ja|新寺町 (弘前市)|12=draft}} area
* [[Miyagi Prefecture]]: [[Sendai]] - {{ill|Shintera|ja|新寺 (若林区)|12=draft}}, Wakabayashi Ward
* [[Akita Prefecture]]: [[Akita City]] - {{ill|Kyokuhoku|ja|旭北寺町|12=draft}} area

; Kanto Region
* [[Chiba Prefecture]]: [[Funabashi]] - {{ill|Motomachi Teramachi|ja|本町寺町|12=draft}}
* [[Tokyo]]:
** [[Minato City]] - {{ill|Mita|ja|三田 (東京都港区)|12=draft}} Fourth Chome (see [[Tsukino Misaki]])
** [[Taito City]] - {{ill|Yanaka|ja|谷中 (台東区)|12=draft}}
** [[Setagaya]] - {{ill|Karasuyama Teramachi|ja|烏山寺町|12=draft}}
** [[Hachioji]] - {{ill|Teramachi (Hachioji)|ja|寺町 (八王子市)|12=draft}}

; Chubu Region
