{{Confused|Jinaimachi}}

'''Teramachi''' (寺町) refers to areas in Japan where [[temples]] are concentrated. This name can be found in cities across Japan. In many [[castle towns]], temples and [[cemeteries]] were grouped on the outskirts of the city to form a defensive line in case of enemy attacks.

== Major Teramachi Locations ==
; Tohoku Region
* [[Aomori Prefecture]]: [[Hirosaki]] - Nishishigemori area ({{ill|Zenrin Street|ja|禅林街|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), {{ill|Niideramachi|ja|新寺町 (弘前市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}} area
* [[Miyagi Prefecture]]: [[Sendai]] - {{ill|Shintera|ja|新寺 (若林区)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Wakabayashi Ward
