{{Confused|Jinaimachi}}

'''Teramachi''' (寺町) refers to areas in Japan where [[temples]] are concentrated. This name can be found in cities across Japan. In many [[Walled City|Castle towns]], temples and [[cemeteries]] were grouped on the outskirts of the city to form a defensive line in case of enemy attacks.

== Major Teramachi Locations ==
; Tohoku Region
* [[Aomori Prefecture]]: [[Hirosaki]] - Nishishigemori area ({{ill|Zenrin Street|ja|禅林街|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zenrin Street|qq=}}), {{ill|Niideramachi|ja|新寺町 (弘前市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Niideramachi|qq=}} area
* [[Miyagi Prefecture]]: [[Sendai]] - {{ill|Shintera|ja|新寺 (若林区)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shintera|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, Wakabayashi Ward
* [[Akita Prefecture]]: [[Akita City]] - {{ill|Kyokuhoku|ja|旭北寺町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyokuhoku|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} area

