{{Confused|Jinaimachi}}

'''Teramachi''' (寺町) refers to areas in Japan where [[temples]] are concentrated. This name can be found in cities across Japan. In many [[Walled City|Castle towns]], temples and [[:en:cemeteries|cemeteries]] were grouped on the outskirts of the city to form a defensive line in case of enemy attacks.

