{{Confused|Jinaimachi}}

'''Teramachi''' (寺町) refers to areas in Japan where {{ill|Buddhist temples in Japan|en|Buddhist temples in Japan|WD=Q3141900|lt=Buddhist temples in Japan|1=Buddhist temples in Japan}} are concentrated. This name can be found in cities across Japan. In many [[Walled City|Castle towns]], temples and [[:en:cemeteries|cemeteries]] were grouped on the outskirts of the city to form a defensive line in case of enemy attacks.

